Overview
- setCompressionType(String type) selects the compression method. Valid values are the ones returned by getCompressionTypes() on the ImageWriteParam for the chosen writer/format.
- The default compression type is determined by the writer/format; to customize, enable explicit mode and set both type and quality as needed.
- Not all formats/writers support compression types or quality; if getCompressionTypes() returns null or empty, do not call setCompressionType.
- Common constants used:
  - ImageWriteParam.MODE_EXPLICIT, MODE_DEFAULT, or MODE_COPY_FROM_METADATA (depending on the API version) to control compression mode.
- writeCompressionQuality (via setCompressionQuality) is typically a float between 0.0 and 1.0.
- The actual format determines valid types. For example, JPEG may have "JPEG" as a type; PNG may use "Deflate". Always query getCompressionTypes() for the writer/format you’re using.

Suggested workflow
1) Obtain a writer for the desired format.
2) Get the default ImageWriteParam from the writer.
3) Inspect param.getCompressionTypes() to discover valid types.
4) If types exist, set:
   - param.setCompressionMode(ImageWriteParam.MODE_EXPLICIT);
   - param.setCompressionType(chosenType);
   - param.setCompressionQuality(quality); // 0.0f to 1.0f
5) Write the image with the configured param.

Example (Java)
import javax.imageio.ImageIO;
import javax.imageio.ImageWriteParam;
import javax.imageio.ImageWriter;
import javax.imageio.IIOImage;
import javax.imageio.stream.ImageOutputStream;
import java.awt.image.BufferedImage;
import java.io.File;
import java.io.IOException;

public void writeImageWithCompression(BufferedImage image, File outFile, String imageFormat, float quality) throws IOException {
    ImageWriter writer = null;
    ImageOutputStream ios = null;
    try {
        writer = ImageIO.getImageWritersByFormatName(imageFormat).next();
        ios = ImageIO.createImageOutputStream(outFile);
        writer.setOutput(ios);

        ImageWriteParam param = writer.getDefaultWriteParam();

        String[] compressionTypes = param.getCompressionTypes();
        if (compressionTypes != null && compressionTypes.length > 0) {
            // Choose a suitable type; here we pick the first available
            String chosenType = compressionTypes[0];
            param.setCompressionMode(ImageWriteParam.MODE_EXPLICIT);
            param.setCompressionType(chosenType);
            param.setCompressionQuality(quality); // 0.0f (lowest) .. 1.0f (best)
        }

        IIOImage iioImage = new IIOImage(image, null, null);
        writer.write(null, iioImage, param);
    } finally {
        if (writer != null) {
            writer.dispose();
        }
        if (ios != null) {
            ios.close();
        }
    }
}

Notes
- The actual valid compression types depend on the format. Use getCompressionTypes() to determine supported options for JPEG, PNG, TIFF, etc.
- If you need a default behavior, you can skip setCompressionType and rely on the writer’s default, but you won’t be able to control the specific compression method.
- DEFAULT_IMAGE_FORMAT (if you’re using a config constant) can be used as a fallback for imageFormat if none is specified, but ensure the value matches a supported writer format name.
